                <div class="menu-2">
                <h3>
                    DONATION PROCESS
                </h3>
                Donating blood is a safe simple , and rewarding experience that usully only takes 45-50 minutes.<br><br>
                
                <h4>1. Before You Donate??</h4>
                To donate blood find a blood bank near you using AABB's blood bank locater. Then call the blood bank to make an appointment. When making the appointment. 
                <h4>2. What are your general donar requirements??</h4>
                (Most places require you to weigh a minimum of 110 ponds. be at leat 16 year-olds and be generally healthy.)
                <h4>3. what kind of identification is required??</h4>
                (First-time donar are usully asked to present two from of identification the type of identification needed varies by faclity.)<br>
                if you have any particular health concerns or have traveled outside of the country.it's also a good idea to inform the blood bank at the time you are making your appoinment 
                <h4>4. When You Arrive at the Blood Donation Center</h4>
                When you sign in,you will be asked to complete a donor registration from. which includes your name. address ,phone number, and various other type of <br>
                demographic information.
                You will also be asked to show your donor card or the type of identification required by the particular blood bank you visit

